Huawei has launched the P Smart 2021 smartphone in South Africa, which offers impressive features at an affordable price. Click here to buy the Huawei P Smart 2021. The P Smart 2021 is designed to be a smart companion for you across an extensive range of digital activities â€“ including mobile photography. The P Smart 2021 uses a Quad AI camera which packs a 48MP primary lens, an 8MP ultra-wide-angle lens, a 2MP macro camera, and a 2MP depth camera. This camera enables high-quality night photography thanks to its impressive 48MP primary sensor as well as AI-assisted multi-frame noise reduction technology. Night mode also supports photography stabilisation for up to six seconds of exposure to increase the dynamic range and brightness of photographs taken in low-light conditions. The 8MP ultra-wide camera then offers a 120-degree field of view which enables you to fit everything (or everyone) into a single photograph. This makes the P Smart 2021 great for taking photos of groups and landscapes. The 2MP macro camera allows you to take close-up photos from up to 4cm away, while a 2MP depth camera allows you to create a variety of aperture effects that blur the background out in the photos you take. The P Smart 2021 also has an impressive 8MP selfie camera that makes it easy to take photos of yourself in a variety of conditions and supports a variety of AI beauty features. The P Smart 2021 offers impressive hardware that makes it a great option within its price range. This includes a 6.67-inch 2,400 x 1,080 display, 128GB of built-in storage, MicroSD support for up to 512GB, a Kirin 710A processor, 4GB of RAM, and large 5,000mAh battery. The Huawei P Smart 2021 is secured through a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, while this smartphone has a USB Type-C port and a 3.5mm headphone jack. The Huawei P Smart 2021 is now available in South Africa for just R5,999 from the Huawei Store. As part of this great deal, you also receive a free powerbank, 100 days of screen care, and 1